From 61fffdaac20f98499f8cc2540b063ef5baf41860 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kierandrewett <kieran@drewett.dev>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 14:34:13 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(grants): persist exact portal permissions

Replace basename marker grants with portal-scoped, namespaced identities derived from the trusted frontend request. Store typed ScreenCast and RemoteDesktop capabilities under XDG_DATA_HOME and replay only the exact approved monitor, device, and clipboard set.

Hide remember controls when the requester cannot be verified or the selected source shape cannot be restored safely. Delay writes until Mutter reports the session ready, clear pending grants on cancellation and close, and report clipboard enable failures instead of persisting them.

Validated with the xdg-desktop-portal-gnome Meson build and the gnoblin-portal-grants test covering direct-backend spoof rejection, host identity resolution, portal scoping, strict grant validation, round trips, and digest collision resistance.
